flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|concentrated|deep_focus|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Better ideas after focused work|You are most likely to find flow when you have time to stay with one demanding thing before opening it up.|This pattern often shows up when you need quiet time to understand the work properly. You may reread the brief, sit with the problem, or build a first version alone before you want input. Creative Movement then helps the work loosen and develop. Physical Rhythm helps when concentration starts to feel heavy. Social Exchange becomes useful when the idea needs to make sense to someone else.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::concentrated
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|paired|deep_focus|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Considered ideas with room to move|You are most likely to find flow when focused thinking and idea movement can work together.|This pattern often shows up when you need enough quiet to understand the problem, but not so much structure that the work becomes fixed too early. You may move between careful attention and fresh angles until the work starts to feel both solid and alive. Physical Rhythm can help when attention gets heavy or static. Social Exchange becomes useful when the work needs to be tested outside your own process.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::paired
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|graduated|deep_focus|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Focus, then ideas, then reset|You are likely to find flow through a clear sequence: settle into the work, let ideas develop, then use movement and feedback when the pattern needs range.|This result may feel recognisable if you prefer to understand the problem before trying different angles. Creative Movement gives the work freshness once Deep Focus has found the substance. Physical Rhythm can help when attention becomes heavy. Social Exchange is useful when the work needs checking outside your own process.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::graduated
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|balanced|deep_focus|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Several ways into flow|You are likely to find flow through different conditions depending on the work in front of you.|Deep Focus appears first, but not by enough to make the result one-sided. You may use quiet concentration, fresh ideas, movement, or conversation at different points. The useful question is not which signal defines you. It is which condition the work needs now.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::balanced
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_social_exchange_physical_rhythm|concentrated|deep_focus|creative_movement|social_exchange|physical_rhythm|Focused work that needs a response|You are most likely to find flow when you can think deeply first, then open the work through ideas and useful feedback.|This pattern often shows up when you want time to understand the work before anyone else gets involved. Once the thinking has substance, Creative Movement can help the work become more original, and Social Exchange can test whether it lands. Physical Rhythm may need to be added deliberately when the work starts to feel stuck in your head.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_social_exchange_physical_rhythm::concentrated
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_social_exchange_physical_rhythm|paired|deep_focus|creative_movement|social_exchange|physical_rhythm|Focused thinking with live testing|You are likely to find flow when careful attention and idea movement work closely together, then conversation helps test what the work has become.|This result may feel familiar if your best thinking needs both quiet and range. You may sit with the problem, find a better angle, then want to explain or test it with someone useful. Physical Rhythm sits later in the order, so movement or a change of state may need to be brought in before the work becomes too mental.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_social_exchange_physical_rhythm::paired
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_social_exchange_physical_rhythm|graduated|deep_focus|creative_movement|social_exchange|physical_rhythm|Think, reframe, then test|You are likely to reach flow through a stepped pattern: focus first, ideas second, conversation third, and physical reset when the work needs deliberate range.|This pattern may show up when you want the work to make sense privately before it becomes more expressive or shareable. Creative Movement opens better angles after Deep Focus has done the early work. Social Exchange helps translate the result for another person. Physical Rhythm can help when the process needs a reset rather than more thinking or more talk.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_social_exchange_physical_rhythm::graduated
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_social_exchange_physical_rhythm|balanced|deep_focus|creative_movement|social_exchange|physical_rhythm|Depth, ideas, and response|You may find flow through several routes, with focus first but ideas and conversation close enough to matter.|This result should be read lightly. You may sometimes need quiet concentration, sometimes a fresh angle, and sometimes a useful conversation to make the work clearer. Physical Rhythm is still part of the profile, especially when the work needs a change of state rather than another round of thinking.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_social_exchange_physical_rhythm::balanced
flow-state|deep_focus_physical_rhythm_creative_movement_social_exchange|concentrated|deep_focus|physical_rhythm|creative_movement|social_exchange|Deep work with a practical rhythm|You are most likely to find flow when focused attention is supported by movement, pace, or a steady physical state.|This pattern often shows up when serious thinking works better with a rhythm around it. You may need quiet time with the task, but also a walk, routine, practical action, or change of setting to keep attention from becoming forced. Creative Movement adds fresh angles once the work has traction. Social Exchange helps test the result when it needs to make sense to someone else.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_physical_rhythm_creative_movement_social_exchange::concentrated
flow-state|deep_focus_physical_rhythm_creative_movement_social_exchange|paired|deep_focus|physical_rhythm|creative_movement|social_exchange|Focused attention with movement beside it|You are likely to find flow when concentration and physical rhythm work together.|This result may feel recognisable if sitting still and thinking harder is not always the best route into deep work. You may need a practical rhythm, a change of pace, or movement around the task so attention can settle. Creative Movement can add range once the work is underway. Social Exchange may be useful when the result needs outside response.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_physical_rhythm_creative_movement_social_exchange::paired
flow-state|deep_focus_physical_rhythm_creative_movement_social_exchange|graduated|deep_focus|physical_rhythm|creative_movement|social_exchange|Focus that moves before it opens|You are likely to reach flow through a clear order: focus deeply, use rhythm to stay engaged, then bring in ideas and feedback.|This pattern may show up when you need serious attention but also need the body or environment to help that attention keep working. Physical Rhythm gives Deep Focus a way to recover before the work gets heavy. Creative Movement adds new angles once the task has momentum. Social Exchange becomes useful when the work needs testing beyond your own view.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_physical_rhythm_creative_movement_social_exchange::graduated
flow-state|deep_focus_physical_rhythm_creative_movement_social_exchange|balanced|deep_focus|physical_rhythm|creative_movement|social_exchange|Several ways to stay with the work|You may find flow through focus, rhythm, ideas, or conversation depending on what the task needs.|Deep Focus appears first, but Physical Rhythm and Creative Movement are close enough to matter. You may need quiet concentration for one task, a change of pace for another, and a fresh angle when the work starts to narrow. Social Exchange can still help when the result needs to be checked with someone else.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_physical_rhythm_creative_movement_social_exchange::balanced
flow-state|deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange_creative_movement|concentrated|deep_focus|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|creative_movement|Steady focus before new angles|You are most likely to find flow when deep attention is held steady by rhythm, then tested through useful exchange.|This pattern often shows up when you want the work to become solid and practical before it becomes more experimental. Physical Rhythm helps attention stay usable, especially when the task is demanding. Social Exchange can check whether the work makes sense beyond your own process. Creative Movement may need deliberate room so the result does not become too fixed too soon.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange_creative_movement::concentrated
flow-state|deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange_creative_movement|paired|deep_focus|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|creative_movement|Deep work with steady momentum|You are likely to find flow when concentration and physical rhythm support each other closely.|This result may feel familiar if you need both mental depth and a steady working pace. You may focus best when the setting, routine, or body state helps attention stay available. Social Exchange can test the work before it becomes too enclosed. Creative Movement may need to be invited earlier when the work needs more range or originality.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange_creative_movement::paired
flow-state|deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange_creative_movement|graduated|deep_focus|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|creative_movement|Focus, rhythm, then response|You are likely to reach flow through a stepped pattern where attention settles first, rhythm keeps it usable, and conversation tests the result.|This pattern may show up when the work needs depth, steadiness, and a practical check before it needs a new angle. Physical Rhythm helps Deep Focus avoid becoming static. Social Exchange brings in response when the work needs to be understood by someone else. Creative Movement is useful range when the result becomes too fixed or purely practical.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange_creative_movement::graduated
flow-state|deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange_creative_movement|balanced|deep_focus|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|creative_movement|Flexible focus with practical checks|You may find flow through several close routes, with focus lightly first and rhythm, exchange, and ideas all still meaningful.|This result should not be read as one route doing all the work. Some tasks may need quiet depth. Others may need movement, a useful conversation, or permission to try a different angle. The pattern becomes clearest when you choose the condition the work needs now rather than defaulting to more focus.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange_creative_movement::balanced
flow-state|deep_focus_social_exchange_creative_movement_physical_rhythm|concentrated|deep_focus|social_exchange|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|Private thought that sharpens through response|You are most likely to find flow when serious thinking comes first and conversation helps sharpen what the work is becoming.|This pattern often shows up when you want time to understand the issue before talking it through. Once the thinking has weight, Social Exchange can help test, translate, or refine it. Creative Movement adds range so the work does not become too narrow. Physical Rhythm may need to be added deliberately when attention gets heavy or stuck.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_social_exchange_creative_movement_physical_rhythm::concentrated
flow-state|deep_focus_social_exchange_creative_movement_physical_rhythm|paired|deep_focus|social_exchange|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|Focused thought with useful exchange|You are likely to find flow when deep thinking and conversation work closely together.|This result may feel recognisable if you need private attention first, but the work becomes clearer when you explain it, test it, or hear a useful response. Creative Movement can add fresh angles after the exchange opens the work up. Physical Rhythm may be useful when the process needs a reset rather than more thinking or more discussion.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_social_exchange_creative_movement_physical_rhythm::paired
flow-state|deep_focus_social_exchange_creative_movement_physical_rhythm|graduated|deep_focus|social_exchange|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|Think first, test next|You are likely to reach flow through a clear order: focus privately, test the work through conversation, then bring in ideas and movement when needed.|This pattern may show up when the work needs both depth and response. Deep Focus helps you find your own line of thought. Social Exchange checks whether that thinking is clear outside your own head. Creative Movement adds range after the work has been tested. Physical Rhythm can help when the process needs a change of state.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_social_exchange_creative_movement_physical_rhythm::graduated
flow-state|deep_focus_social_exchange_creative_movement_physical_rhythm|balanced|deep_focus|social_exchange|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|Several routes, with response close by|You may find flow through focus, conversation, ideas, or movement depending on what the work needs.|Deep Focus appears first, but Social Exchange and Creative Movement are close enough to matter. You may need quiet time to understand the work, then a useful conversation to test it, or a fresh angle to keep it developing. Physical Rhythm still matters when the work needs a reset rather than another round of thinking.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_social_exchange_creative_movement_physical_rhythm::balanced
flow-state|deep_focus_social_exchange_physical_rhythm_creative_movement|concentrated|deep_focus|social_exchange|physical_rhythm|creative_movement|Focused thinking before shared clarity|You are most likely to find flow when deep attention comes first and conversation helps make the thinking clearer.|This pattern often shows up when you prefer to understand the work privately before bringing someone else in. Social Exchange can sharpen the result once there is enough substance to discuss. Physical Rhythm helps reset the process when attention gets heavy. Creative Movement may need deliberate space so the work does not become too settled too early.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_social_exchange_physical_rhythm_creative_movement::concentrated
flow-state|deep_focus_social_exchange_physical_rhythm_creative_movement|paired|deep_focus|social_exchange|physical_rhythm|creative_movement|Deep thought that needs a sounding board|You are likely to find flow when focused thinking and useful exchange sit close together.|This result may feel familiar if the work starts privately but becomes stronger when it is spoken, questioned, or tested with one useful person. Physical Rhythm can help when the process needs a reset or change of state. Creative Movement may need to be invited when the work needs a less obvious angle.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_social_exchange_physical_rhythm_creative_movement::paired
flow-state|deep_focus_social_exchange_physical_rhythm_creative_movement|graduated|deep_focus|social_exchange|physical_rhythm|creative_movement|Focus, response, then reset|You are likely to reach flow through a sequence where deep attention comes first, conversation tests it, movement resets it, and ideas add range.|This pattern may show up when you need to think carefully before using another person as a sounding board. Social Exchange helps the work become clearer outside your own process. Physical Rhythm can keep the pattern from becoming too mental. Creative Movement is useful when the result needs more possibility or a different angle.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_social_exchange_physical_rhythm_creative_movement::graduated
flow-state|deep_focus_social_exchange_physical_rhythm_creative_movement|balanced|deep_focus|social_exchange|physical_rhythm|creative_movement|Flexible flow with a clear thinking base|You may find flow through several close conditions, with focus first but conversation, movement, and ideas all available.|This balanced result may show up when different tasks need different routes. Some work needs quiet attention. Some needs a useful conversation. Some needs a physical reset or a fresh angle. Deep Focus is the first place to look, but the pattern works best when you treat the other routes as real options.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_social_exchange_physical_rhythm_creative_movement::balanced
flow-state|creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|concentrated|creative_movement|deep_focus|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Original ideas with enough focus to land|You are most likely to find flow when ideas can move, connect, and turn into a direction worth following.|This pattern often shows up when you need room to explore before the work becomes fixed. You may sketch a rough version, try a less obvious angle, or notice links that other people have not seen yet. Deep Focus then helps you stay with the strongest idea long enough to make it useful. Physical Rhythm can clear space when too many possibilities start to crowd the work. Social Exchange becomes useful when the idea needs to be tested with another person.|active|flow-state::creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::concentrated
flow-state|creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|paired|creative_movement|deep_focus|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Ideas that gain substance|You are likely to find flow when idea movement and focused attention work closely together.|This result may feel familiar if you need a fresh angle first, then enough concentration to make the best idea hold. You may move through rough versions, links, or possibilities before choosing one to develop. Physical Rhythm can help when too many ideas are active at once. Social Exchange is useful when the work needs to be checked outside your own process.|active|flow-state::creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::paired
flow-state|creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|graduated|creative_movement|deep_focus|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Ideas, then focus, then reset|You are likely to reach flow through a clear order: let ideas move, focus the strongest one, reset when the work gets crowded, then test it with someone useful.|This pattern may show up when possibility is the way in, but the work still needs depth before it becomes useful. Deep Focus gives the best idea time and weight. Physical Rhythm can clear mental clutter when the process becomes too busy. Social Exchange helps you see whether the idea lands with another person.|active|flow-state::creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::graduated
flow-state|creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|balanced|creative_movement|deep_focus|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Several routes for original work|You may find flow through ideas, focus, movement, or conversation depending on the task in front of you.|Creative Movement appears first, but not by enough to make the result one-sided. Some work may need a fresh angle. Some may need quiet attention, a change of pace, or a useful response from another person. The useful question is which condition helps the idea become clearer now.|active|flow-state::creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::balanced
flow-state|creative_movement_deep_focus_social_exchange_physical_rhythm|concentrated|creative_movement|deep_focus|social_exchange|physical_rhythm|Ideas that need depth and response|You are most likely to find flow when ideas can open first, then gain substance and be tested with another person.|This pattern often shows up when the work starts through links, possibilities, or a less obvious route. Deep Focus helps the strongest idea become more than an interesting start. Social Exchange can test whether the idea is clear, useful, and easy to explain. Physical Rhythm may need to be added deliberately when the process becomes too mental or static.|active|flow-state::creative_movement_deep_focus_social_exchange_physical_rhythm::concentrated
